    "title": "Career Opportunity Medical Officer at Alkem Laboratories",
    "description": "Alkem Laboratories has an exciting opening for a Medical Officer at our Bengaluru office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Alkem Laboratories:\nAlkem Laboratories is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Monitor patient progress and adjust treatment plans accordingly\n• Ensure patient privacy and maintain confidentiality\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 10-15 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Ethics\n• Proficiency in CPT Codes\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n• Proficiency in Health Informatics\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Learning & development budget\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 20 LPA - 40 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Bengaluru, Karnataka, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Alkem Laboratories!",
